        "exhibitionLabelText": {
            "en": {
                "purposes": [
                    "The Weight of Lightness"
                ],
                "labels": [
                    {
                        "purpose": "The Weight of Lightness",
                        "text": "Liu Kuo-sung, a founder of the Taiwanese modernist art group Fifth Moon Society (1956–1972), defined his oeuvre by creating paintings that evoked the feeling of landscape without literally depicting them. He created a dynamic in this painting by maintaining a balance between the marked and unmarked areas, an important aesthetic principle in classical Chinese landscape painting. The feathery white marks that provide the zigzag form in the painting a texture and motion are the results of peeling off fibres from coarse cotton paper, a signature technique Liu developed in 1963 to replace the textured strokes in traditional paintings."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "zh-hant": {
                "purposes": [
                    "The Weight of Lightness"
                ],
                "labels": [
                    {
                        "purpose": "The Weight of Lightness",
                        "text": "劉國松是台灣現代藝術團體「五月畫會」（1956–1972年）的創立者之一，作品大多意溢乎形，以營造出山水的意境。作品裏落筆和留白間的和諧平衡，是中國古典山水畫的重要美學原則。他於1963年獨創「抽筋剝皮皴」技法，以粗綿紙上撕下紙筋，代替傳統水墨中的飛白效果，輕柔的白色痕跡在畫面形成曲折的造形，紋理豐沛，饒富動感。"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    },
